# Ex 24: Allow subject slot to be dropped for 3sg pronoun for intransitive verb
Source: a:95
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {argument optionality}
Nagsukat
n-ag-sukat
PF-I-change
`he changed`

# Ex 25: Subject slot should exist for transitive verb
Source: a:31
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {argument optionality}
Nakitan=ak
na-kita=na=ak
PF.T-see =3sE =1sA
She saw me

# Ex 26: Object can be dropped for transitive verb when obj is 3sg absolutive pronoun
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {argument optionality}
Nakita=na
na-kita=na
PF.T-see=3sE
She saw it

# Ex 27: Object can be dropped for transitive verb when obj is 3sg absolutive pronoun
Source: a:419
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {argument optionality}
Kayatko
kayat=ko
want=1sE
I want it

