# grammatically correct possessive, using absolutive enclitic pronoun
Source: a:117
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {possessives}
Nakita ti babai ti balay=ko
nakita CORE.sg babai CORE.sg house=1s.Abs.Enc
saw the girl my house
`The girl saw her house'

# incorrect case for possessive, using ergative enclitic pronoun
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {case}
Nakita ti babai ti balay=ak
nakita CORE.sg babai CORE.sg balay=1s.Abs.Erg
saw the girl my house
`The girl saw my house house'


